post_text: One of our teachers Whitney McCain shares the impact SLACS has had on her over the course of 5 years. "I enjoy coming to work. The kids were a lot of fun. My mentor teacher has taught me so much. I knew I was in a environment I know I can grow in. The environment promoted creativity and I knew from there, this is somewhere I wanted to be as well as work at for a long time. I've been here for 5 years and I am happy to be here." At Southwest Leadership Academy, we have a tight knit community where new educators can flourish like Ms. McCain has or even create meaningful relationships with students. To learn more about us, check out our website: www.slacs-phila.org

post_text:
Southwest Leadership Academy’s buildings and offices will be closed Friday, June 19,2020 in celebration of the Juneteenth Holiday.

From Mental Floss: On June 19, 1865, General Gordon Granger rode into Galveston, Texas, and announced enslaved people were now free. Since then, June 19 has been celebrated as Juneteenth across the nation. The June 19 announcement came more than two and a half years after Abraham Lincoln issued the Emancipation Proclamation on January 1, 1863. So technically, from the Union's perspective, the 250,000 enslaved people in Texas were already free—but none of them were aware of it, and no one was in a rush to inform them. On this day, we celebrate freedom.

Today is Monday April 20, 2020. I hope that you and your family are well and in good spirits.

As we settle in to our new normal, it’s important to find ways to manage stress. Focus on things that are within your control and rest when you are able to.

If you are able to join your Zoom classes on time, please make sure that you do so. If not, the session will be posted to your Google Classroom.

Keep following the Governor and Mayor’s stay at home order. Only travel for life sustaining tasks. You are permitted to go outside for exercise. It’s going to be another beautiful day today. Make sure that you get outside for some fresh air and sunshine.

The parent email went out at 8:00 today as usual. Please refer to the email for times to come in today to pick up your child(ren)’s belongings.

Follow @slacs_climate_team for additional information and activities!

Be well and have a wonderful day!

Ms. Purnell

Good Morning!

Today is Monday April 13,2020. I hope that you and your family are well and in good spirits.

Students, make sure that you join your Zoom sessions today! If you miss it, your teacher will post the video each day.

Follow @slacs_climate_team for additional information and activities!

Governor Wolf and Secretary Rivera have announced that remote learning will continue through the end of the year.

Parents, If you have provided an email address, you will receive an email from me at 8:00 this morning.

Governor Wolf and Mayor Kenney have issued a stay at home order. That means that you should only go out to run errands for needs like groceries or a doctor’s appointment. You are also allowed to go outside to get some exercise.

Make reading for 30 minutes a goal for today! Parents, if you have time, find a book or magazine and join your child for their 30 minutes of reading today.

Have a good day!

Be Well,
Ms. Purnell

post_text:
Good Morning!

Today is Thursday March 26,2020. I hope that you and your family are well and in good spirits.

No classes tomorrow. Teachers have a Professional Development Day.

Parents, If you have provided an email address, you will receive an email from me at 8:00 this morning. Make sure that you sing along with the Announcements video today!

Governor Wolf and Mayor Kenney have issued a stay at home order. That means that you should only go out to run errands for needs like groceries or a doctor’s appointment. You are also allowed to go outside to get some exercise.

Make reading for 30 minutes a goal for today! Parents, if you have time, find a book or magazine and join your child for their 30 minutes of reading today.

Make sure that you get outside and get some fresh air and sunshine

Have a good day!

Be Well,
Ms. Purnell

post_text:
Dear Students,
Good Morning!

Today is Thursday March 19, 2020

I hope that this finds you doing well and in good spirits.

I know that there are many reports that you are seeing on the news and on social media. It’s important to understand the difference between what’s real and what someone has made up. You’ve learned about facts and opinions, make sure that you listen to the facts!

I am proud of you and the work that you are doing with your teachers and parents on Google Classroom and in your packets.

Make sure that you are reading every day and go outside to get some fresh air and exercise.

I miss you all and I look forward to seeing you soon! Ms. Purnell

By order of the Governor, our school will be closed Monday, March 16 - March 27. Tentatively we are resuming classes Monday, March 30.
Message from our CAO/Principal Ms. Purnell: "We understand the difficulties the mandated building closure has on our families. Because the health and safety of our students and staff are extremely important to us, we agree the closure is for the best. Thank you for your understanding. We are in this together and we will get through this together."

post_text: A message from our CAO/Principal Leigh Purnell: Southwest Leadership Academy Charter School is in Pursuit of Excellence! We strive every day to be better than we were the day before. As we partner in the education of your child, please remember to read with your child every night. Even if your child reads independently, try to take the 20 minutes each evening to sit down and read something while they are completing their daily reading assignment. Please get involved in the life of our school. Our Home and School Association is a great place to start! There will also be opportunities to volunteer during the school day as well as to chaperone field trips. I’m looking forward to more opportunities to interact with you. Let’s partner together as we continue on our journey to make Southwest Leadership the best K-8 in the City of Philadelphia!

post_text: Know the facts about where candidates stand on education and make sure you are registered to vote! Our future leaders are right here at SLA, but for today we need to teach our children by example. Talk to them about the importance of voting and the need for a well-funded public education system that allows for public school choice!
